fields.title: Giant Reign for Sale
fields.description:
I'm selling my 2013 Giant Reign 2 all-mountain bike with full suspension, dropper seat, and upgraded back wheel. The frame size is large. I have thoroughly enjoyed this bike and taken great care of it, and while I want to move to a more conservative, cross-country or general trail riding bike, this Giant has not only served its purpose while climbing but really excelled when descending. A couple of things:

I replaced the derailleur about a year ago with the same Sram X7.

I upgraded the back wheel with a DT Swiss XR 4.1d, handbuilt by a bike mechanic at the now-extinct Gusto Cycles.

I am including the Deity Compound pedals with the bike.

I'm also throwing in the suspension pump that you see in the one of the pictures.

Take a look at the specs online and let me know if you have any questions. I am able to meet pretty much anywhere in Greenville, but if you're coming from out of town, we can make arrangements for that as well. 
Thanks, Jonathan

fields.title: 2011 Cannondale Synapse 6, 54cm Road Bik
fields.description:
2011 Cannondale Synapse 6, 54cm Price drop to $575
Looking for a great road bike? This bike is the perfect choice. 
I am very sad to be selling this bike, but decided to make the switch to a Cyclocross bike so I can join my husband in racing CX. That being said I have taken meticulous care of this bike (it has been kept in our house) and all maintenance has been done by a very professional local bike shop. The ride on this bike is VERY comfortable both on longer rides and is great for climbing (I loved riding the Blue Ridge Parkway on this bike). It also has great stability, handling, and shifts perfectly. Recent maintenance include: new brake cables, cable housing, chain, cassette, low mile tires, and brake pads. Please let me know if you have any questions or would like to take it for a test ride!

Here is Cannondale's description of the bike:
Synapse aluminum frame is built to give riders great handling, stability and steering precision for an excellent all-around road ride quality. Seatstays and carbon fork feature the Cannondale Synapse Active Vibration Elimination (S.A.V.E.) technology for damping road vibration 9-speed drivetrain features Shimano Tiagra crank set and components for dependable shifts across the 18 gear combinations
